                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Fine, sometimes uneven.</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black (deep reddish brown on fols. 46ra l.16-48rb l. 9), red</seg>
                        <date>15th-16th century (?)</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: fols. 1r-34v, 58r-156r, broadly spaced letters (except fols. 24va-26vb, 28ra-34ra, 58r-74v) with curved left-sloping letter shapes.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
Peculiar features:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
- ደ has the 6th order marker slanted to the left<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">
- የ has the 7th order marker usually slanted to the left<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic">
- the loop marking the 5th order is sometimes open.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic">
<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic">
Hand b: fols. 35r-57v, characterized by angular right-sloping letter shapes.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h9" script="Ethiopic">
It is possible that another hand was involved in the writing (s. e.g., fols. 58r-74v).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h10" script="Ethiopic">
Particular features:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h11" script="Ethiopic">
- the upper horizontal stroke of መ is usually slanted to the left<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h12" script="Ethiopic">
- ፀ has a rectangular shape, esp. in the 5th order<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h13" script="Ethiopic">
- መ has the loops usually not separated, esp. in the 4th order.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
